laboratory_examinations.findings: Specimens from the right axillary mass and an acral erythematous papule demonstrated BCC with infiltrative and morpheiform features.
Demonstrated one new extrathoracic lymph node and slight enlargement of another, while other lymph nodes were stable.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Increased size of one lymph node and new lymph node found, overall stable status of the other lymph nodes.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Negative for bacteria, fungi, or atypical mycobacteria.
